{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.9. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}]}],"name":"Important"},{"text":"Sharing state","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Sharing-state"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This will require that ","type":"text"},{"code":"SignUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes of ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"key:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Similar to ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", upon launch of the application the initial","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be automatically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference"},{"text":" article","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for more detailed information.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"type":"text","tex